        "id": "MP-150",
        "type": "analytics",
        "status": "done",
        "priority": "P2",
        "title": "CAPM Risk-Decomposition Analyzer — Jensen's Alpha, Treynor Ratio & Modigliani M² (read-only/advisory)",
        "sprint": "v4.65",
        "completed_at": "2026-06-12",
        "completed_by": "claude (SPA-V465)",
        "depends_on": [
          "MP-115",
          "MP-394",
          "MP-501"
        ],
        "description": "CAPM benchmark-relative risk decomposition extending benchmark_comparison.py (MP-394) with the risk-adjusted metrics it omitted. Regress portfolio excess return (Rp-Rf) on benchmark excess return (Rm-Rf): beta=cov(Rp,Rm)/var(Rm); Jensen's alpha = mean(Rp)-[Rf+beta*(mean(Rm)-Rf)] (CAPM intercept, annualized geometrically at 365/yr); Treynor=(ann_Rp-ann_Rf)/beta; Modigliani M2 (RAP)=ann_Rf+sharpe_p*sigma_bench_annual with m2_alpha=M2-ann_benchmark; appraisal_ratio=alpha_daily/std(residuals)*sqrt(365); systematic/specific variance split (systematic=beta^2*var(Rm), specific=pvar(residuals), capm_r_squared, pct_systematic_risk); plus beta & correlation. Default flat risk-free benchmark (4.0%) has zero variance -> all CAPM metrics None/ok with honest note; varying benchmark_returns populates everything. Advisory verdict {ok,warn} from annualized Jensen alpha (>=2% ok, <=-2% warn) with <40-obs low-sample cap. MIN_OBS=20. Pure stdlib OLS/cov/var from scratch, read-only, atomic idempotent write, reuses extract_equity_series + content_fingerprint by import. 90 tests, llm_forbidden_lint clean."
      },
