          "MP-501"
        ],
        "description": "Upside Potential Ratio (Sortino, van der Meer & Plantinga 1999) = upside_potential / downside_deviation about MAR=0, both over ALL n returns. UP = mean(max(r-MAR,0)) (order-1 upper partial moment); DD = sqrt(mean(min(r-MAR,0)^2)) (sqrt of order-2 lower partial moment); UPR = UP/DD with natural 1.0 reference. UPR<0.5 -> fail; UPR<1.0 -> warn. Low-sample guard caps fail->warn when <3 downside obs; degenerate (no downside, DD=0) -> UPR=None/ok. Reuses drawdown_analytics.extract_equity_series + tear_sheet.content_fingerprint by import. Pure stdlib, read-only, atomic write, idempotent, 73 tests."
      },
